This document does not contain all approved copy variations, rather is intended to provide a single and consistently updated resource for key product messaging.

| AM-02™: Product Messaging Overview |  |

| Problem Statement | **Fatigue**, **brain fog**, and **low energy** aren’t just inconveniences—they’re the top barriers to daily **performance**. In fact, studies show nearly 8 in 10 Americans go through the day in a fog that interferes with their jobs, their moods and their relationships.1 To keep up, many turn to caffeine-loaded solutions like **coffee**, **energy drinks**, or generic **supplements** with dubious clinical support. While these products can sometimes deliver a temporary lift, they often lead to side effects such as **jitters**, **energy crashes**, and **disrupted sleep**. That’s because most quick fixes spike **cortisol** and overstimulate the nervous system—leaving you more drained in the long run. [1](https://aasm.org/daytime-sleepiness-takes-toll-americans-impacting-daily-life/)American Sleep Academy  |

A cycle of brain fog, crashes, and burnout. AM-02™ Energy \+ Focus **enhances focus**, **sharpens attention**, and **fights fatigue** by targeting the gut-brain axis, with clinically studied **nootropics**.  Powered by ViaCap®, Seed’s proprietary capsule-in-capsule technology, AM-02™ works in collaboration with the microbiome. ## Retail Messaging Hierarchy • AM-02™  Energy \+ Focus {#retail-messaging-hierarchy-•-am-02™-energy-+-focus}

Purpose: Simplify AM-02™’s product narrative for the retail channel based on shopper insights.

Suggested use: 

* Target PDP  
* Target ads  
* Target in-store displays

Audience Summary:   
The Target shopper is fundamentally different from our core DTC member. This persona (female, 25-44) is a busy mom who values family, health and wellness, balancing her time between caring for her children, running errands, and preparing meals. Health and wellness is important to her, but she often finds it challenging to focus on herself amidst her busy schedule. 

* She is struggling to prioritize her own wellness amidst a busy schedule and family life  
* She experiences **frequent stress** and **sleep deprivation**   
* She is struggling with the energy to do all that she needs to—cook, clean, take care of her kids, find time for herself (rare). She is looking for daily energy  
* She seeks affordable solutions that fit into her busy life and budget

Target is her go to store because it offers the convenience of a “one-stop shop” to get everything she needs. In the supplements aisle, she is looking for immediate, clear benefits before making a purchase decision.

| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |

Fast-acting and long-lasting, AM-02™ helps you feel energized, stay sharp, and clear-headed, improving overall **cognitive performance** so you can reach your **mental peak**. | Energy that Peaks—without the Caffeine Crash.  AM-02™ delivers lasting energy with a **caffeine-free** Multi-Peak Energy Complex and B vitamins. Combining proven ingredients that activate and taper at different times, AM-02™ keeps you sharp and focused and delivers that extra boost when you need it most without the jitters or crash from caffeine. | Engineered for Precision Delivery.  AM-02™ is engineered with Seed’s proprietary ViaCap® technology to ensure targeted delivery, so you and your microbiome can access the benefits. |
| Benefits  | **Energy**  Fast-acting energy in 1 hour Lasting energy for up to 6 hours **Cognitive Performance** Supports cognitive function  **Boosts focus and attention Enhances concentration**, sharpness, and mental agility / processing  | **Caffeine-free** Crash-free Jitter-free **Multi-Peak Energy Complex** Proven nootropic ingredients that activate and taper at just the right intervals  | **Precision Delivery** 2-in-1 formulation engineered with Seed’s proprietary ViaCap® technology \[For You\] Outer capsule delivers active nootropics for sustained energy throughout the day \[For Your Microbiome\] Inner capsule delivers prebiotics \+ postbiotics to the gut microbiome, the base of the gut-brain axis |

### Cognitive Performance

| 🧠Cognitive Performance  |  |
| :---- | :---- |
| Claims | Please note: when using these claims you must retain the operative description: “AM-02™ is formulated to”  GENERAL AM-02™ is formulated to… Improve/ support cognitive function/performance Supports acute and sustained cognitive function  Enhance concentration \+ focus Improve attention  Improve **cognitive performance** with continued use Sustain cognitive clarity Support healthy cognitive function  Perform better under cognitive pressure Help you **stay sharp** during cognitive challenges  Support **mental stamina** with continued use  Activates/stimulates \[prefrontal\] areas/regions of the brain \[to support cognitive function\]  **Attention \+ Focus** AM-02™ is formulated to… **Enhance concentration \+ focus Support attention** in healthy individuals Support accuracy and focus on tasks requiring quick decisions Support focus and accuracy during tasks requiring sustained attention Support and maintain cognitive function (accuracy and reaction time) with immediate and continued use \[during cognitively challenging/demanding tasks\] Prevent reduction in cognitive function (accuracy and reaction time) when faced with cognitively-demanding tasks/situations  **Neuroprotection/Neurotransmiters** AM-02 is formulated to… Be neuroprotective\* Support neurotransmitter balance\* Disclaimer: *\*Based on in vitro / preclinical data* |
| Scientific Evidence | **General, Attention \+ Focus** In a randomized, placebo-controlled clinical trial investigating the acute and chronic benefits of Cereboost® Ginseng root on mood and cognition in healthy young adults, including in vitro investigation of gut microbiota changes as a possible mechanism of action, it was found that Cereboost® may help improve attention, accuracy, reaction time, and mood, both shortly after taking it and over longer periods of use. In a [randomized, placebo-controlled cross-over study](https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/hup.2756), ginseng was associated with decreased latency in prefrontal SSVEP (steady state visually evoked potentials) during working memory processing.  This indicates that ginseng may help promote efficient neural processing in key areas of the brain to support cognitive functions. Neurotransmitter/Neuroprotection In a preclinical study, Cereboost Ginseng was administered to a mice model for Alzheimer's. Cereboost was found to recover the cognitive function of the mice, and restore neuronal integrity and acetylcholine levels. In an in vitro study, Rb1 and Rg1, the bioactive ginsenosides of ginseng, were found to promote the neurite outgrowth of PC12 neuronal cells.  In addition, the ginsenosides were able to reverse the cell death of SK-N-SH human neuroblastoma cells that were challenged with a neurotoxin (MPTP), indicating a potential neuroprotective effect of the bioactive. |
| Copy Compliance | ✅Ensure all claims are characterized at the ingredient level by using an appropriate qualifier/modifier: AM-02™ is formulated to…  AM-02™ contains ingredients that…   ✅Ensure use of the appropriate disclaimer when using neuroprotective claims: *\*Based on in vitro / preclinical data*  ❌Assign composition-based claim language such as “AM-02™ is clinically validated to…”. Our product is **not** currently clinically proven |
